caption:
Don’t skip on the pasta at this Michelin-starred steakhouse. 🍝

Chef-owner Curtis Stone (@curtisstone) and his team at Gwen (@gwenla) in LA makes fresh pasta every morning to prepare for a packed evening of hungry dinner guests. After mixing eggs, flour, salt, and olive oil combined with some muscle power, Stone transforms these simple ingredients into an elevated pappardelle pasta. The in-house made noodles are served with a creamy sauce, topped with fresh black truffles, shaved tableside. 

Tap the link in bio to watch how Gwen, the restaurant and butcher shop, serves up premium cuts like rib-eye and pork chops.
